<subSubSection id="8F8FE156F1CFB7E6FA9814FB997D7453" lastPageId="446" lastPageNumber="447" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="490D12631F24869946C67C2160F1AC45" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicName id="4486E8F2366F75A21CD35A54E4A49045" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevum">Bembidium laevum</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823a: 88. Type locality: &quot;Arlington [Middlesex County], Mass[achusetts]&quot; (neotype label). Neotype (♀), designated by Lindroth and Freitag (1969: 339), in MCZ [# 33057]. Note. Because Say (1823a: 88) used the epithet 
<emphasis id="F79EA3EFF47EFEEA911CBA5AA552FFAB" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">laevum</emphasis>
with the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="5ED0D9FD9C2BFD9A5E8DDEE7EAF1FB85" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2CB817CE93CCA51D0732CE79377DA0A0" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Bembidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specific name derives from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="FD46CF4D87CF490754981A59750869DE" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">laevus</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="F89FD06B75016DA55A42E253C700837E" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="6558AEA601EBAFB60B5BF829441691F7" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">um</emphasis>
(left, clumsy [figurative]), not from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="B6492292DE4CF59A2E4DE2D99D37D775" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">laevis</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="0C4E155B9515BE74A306012EB2742390" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">e</emphasis>
(smooth). Therefore, used with the feminine generic name 
<taxonomicName id="BF7978EA4EDBE51B2DCECE022B706AAE" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1862" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Polyderis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5D1C44B88E2C3372F028FEC7FC9445CA" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Polyderis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specific name is 
<emphasis id="FF5363368DA8D732E573DBDCD7EE55CC" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">laeva</emphasis>
, not 
<emphasis id="B852C2AFC4A0770C1EDBEE4A62C8B80F" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">laevis</emphasis>
as used by modern authors.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99F09C5A8B53F97339FC009C5B7A9729" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicName id="24362AF827FD6672664E7CE514FCD805" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troglodytes">Bembidium troglodytes</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831: 44. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="E5AEDB1AAAC9187EEACEAA5F3FD3711B" originalValue="«Amérique">&quot;Amerique</normalizedToken>
septentrionale&quot; (original citation). Holotype [by monotypy] in MHNP (Lindroth 1955b: 14). Synonymy established by LeConte (1848: 472), confirmed by Lindroth (1955b: 14).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="209AA9F475A84AA680056491602C8383" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicName id="56AB465373439EDEDC0A5586BE0149F4" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congestus">Tachys congestus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 212. Type locality: &quot;Norfolk, Virginia&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♀), designated by Erwin (1974a: 144), in USNM [# 46962]. Synonymy established by Erwin (1974a: 144).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="80834F9A8DF5F84213D0DC8ABDFC1F10" lastPageId="446" lastPageNumber="447" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicName id="4F253A09FF257C37324230CCA75B855D" baseAuthorityName="Bilimek" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unistriatus">Tachys unistriatus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 212 [primary homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="7B4B4CD112821AFBE8CE2BC5EE98D97B" baseAuthorityName="Bilimek" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unistriatus">
<emphasis id="634C22A1650064BBBB7347C3FE13454D" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Tachys unistriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Putzeys, 1876]. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="09898908912180FD831A380CB89494CB" originalValue="«Pennsylvania»">&quot;Pennsylvania&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation). Lectotype (♂), designated 
<pageBreakToken id="BAF680C8723B0F4C1BE9A3082DDDCECD" pageId="446" pageNumber="447" start="start">by</pageBreakToken>
Erwin (1974a: 144), in USNM [# 46963]. Synonymy established by Erwin (1974a: 144).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DECD48B93D587ED7FA3F7FEE6537B477" pageId="446" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicName id="5FCDCA9D36AF489ADC6C66CDD3F6FD10" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="446" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus">Tachys rectus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 213. Type locality: &quot;Alexandria [Rapides Parish], Louisiana&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♀), designated by Erwin (1974a: 144), in USNM [# 46961]. Synonymy established by Erwin (1974a: 144).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09AC633D8FD6CC913BBB709F6AE55F36" pageId="446" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicName id="495C368B1C7C91289112D5344805D97D" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="446" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flumenalis">Tachys flumenalis</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 213. Type locality: &quot;Vicksburg [Warren County], Mississippi&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♀), designated by Erwin (1974a: 144), in USNM [# 46964]. Synonymy established by Erwin (1974a: 144).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8617A097FE941448A89BB2EE232E7AAA" pageId="446" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicName id="2B66D1A68405BEA1C5AD1D0CEE767461" authorityName="Csiki" authorityYear="1928" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="446" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unistriolatus">Tachys unistriolatus</taxonomicName>
Csiki, 1928: 202. Replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="7FE28326AFBE44F3C1EE76BF191A310A" baseAuthorityName="Bilimek" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="446" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unistriatus">
<emphasis id="A6C3E73F84EF690612CFD50BA782CBCE" italics="true" pageId="446" pageNumber="447">Tachys unistriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DEC338A6D68C42A5F1036A0416AE231F" pageId="446" pageNumber="447" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="46FA279A7F9F4042DFD3A03E8DA78BFA" pageId="446" pageNumber="447">Distribution.</paragraph>
